        ONLY                                                                          = 8694,  -- Only?
        WAAA                                                                          = 8695,  -- Waaa!
        ID_8696                                                                       = 8696,  -- !!!
        GUKOOL_JA_WHAT_ARE_YOU_DOING_HERE                                             = 8697,  -- Gukool Ja! What are you doing here!?
        HEY_YOU_CAN_T_WHAT_IS_WRONG_WITH                                              = 8698,  -- Hey! You can't...! What is wrong with you!?
        GUKOOL_JA_WHY_DO_YOU_DO_THIS                                                  = 8699,  -- Gukool Ja! Why do you do this!?
        ISWEEN_THIS_IS_THE_BEASTMAN_YOU_WERE_TELLING                                  = 8700,  -- Isween! This is the beastman you were telling us about? He doesn't seem very friendly to me!
        HE_WAS_JUST_USING_YOU_FOR_INFORMATION_YOU                                     = 8701,  -- He was just using you for information! You've been had!
        N_NO_IT_CAN_T_BE_HE_SAVED                                                     = 8702,  -- N-no, it can't be... He saved that child once, why would he take her now...?
        THERE_MUST_BE_SOME_MISTAKE_I_I_HAVE                                           = 8703,  -- There must be some mistake. I...I have to speak with him!
        MERCENARIES_FOLLOW_ISWEEN_AND_DON_T_LET_HIM                                   = 8704,  -- Mercenaries! Follow Isween and don't let him out of your sight. That girl's life depends on it!
        ISWEEN_YOU_FOOL_DO_YOU_REALIZE_THE_DEN                                        = 8705,  -- Isween, you fool... Do you realize the den into which you blindly rush?
        MAMOOK_THE_STRONGHOLD_OF_THE_MAMOOL_JA                                        = 8706,  -- Mamook. The stronghold of the Mamool Ja.
        MY_MEN_ARE_TOO_FEW_TO_SURVIVE_A                                               = 8707,  -- My men are too few to survive a foray into that place...
        YOU_MUST_HELP_THEM_MAKE_YOUR_WAY_TO                                           = 8708,  -- You must help them. Make your way to Mamook, I'll be right behind you.
        MAKE_YOUR_WAY_TO_MAMOOK_I_LL_BE                                               = 8709,  -- Make your way to Mamook, I'll be right behind you.
        OH_IT_S_YOU_AGAIN_HM_YOU_HAVE                                                 = 8710,  -- Oh, it's you again. Hm? You have something to say to me?
        I_SEE_SO_YOU_WITNESSED_THE_EVENTS_IN                                          = 8711,  -- I see... So you witnessed the events in Mamook?
        I_HOPE_YOU_DON_T_MAKE_THE_MISTAKE                                             = 8712,  -- I hope you don't make the mistake of thinking I'm a friend to the beastmen.
        YES_I_DO_HAVE_OCCASION_TO_MEET_AND                                            = 8713,  -- Yes, I do have occasion to meet and exchange information with the Mamool Ja.
        I_FIND_THAT_A_CONNECTION_WITH_YOUR_ENEMY                                      = 8714,  -- I find that a connection with your enemy can often work to your advantage. Not all wars are won with brute force.
        I_AM_SIMPLY_PROTECTING_THIS_CITY_THE_BEST                                     = 8715,  -- I am simply protecting this city the best way I know how.
        I_KNEW_FROM_THE_START_THAT_ISWEEN_WAS                                         = 8716,  -- I knew from the start that Isween was meeting with that beastman.
        BUT_WHEN_THE_MAMOOL_JA_FOUND_OUT_THEY                                         = 8717,  -- But when the Mamool Ja found out, they were ready for blood. I had to send you to watch over him for me.
        WITH_A_POWERFUL_ADVENTURER_LIKE_YOU_ON_HIS                                    = 8718,  -- With a powerful adventurer like you on his side, the beastmen would hesitate to strike.
        ISWEEN_CAME_OUT_OF_THIS_UNSCATHED_SO_I                                        = 8719,  -- Isween came out of this unscathed, so I suppose all's well that ends well. And you can't blame me for placing you in danger's path. Isn't that what adventurers are here for?
        YOU_WANT_TO_KNOW_WHAT_HAPPENED_TO_ISWEEN                                      = 8720,  -- You want to know what happened to Isween?
        HE_S_LEFT_MY_UNIT_FOR_GOOD                                                    = 8721,  -- He's left my unit for good.
        HE_STILL_DREAMS_OF_CARRYING_OUT_HIS_FRIEND                                    = 8722,  -- He still dreams of carrying out his friend's wishes, and putting a stop to war...
        I_VE_NEVER_SEEN_ISWEEN_SHINE_WITH_SO                                          = 8723,  -- I've never seen Isween shine with so much conviction. He's like a new person... Heh, who would've thought it?
        DO_YOU_REMEMBER_THE_SAYING_I_TOLD_YOU                                         = 8724,  -- Do you remember the saying I told you, A tiny hole can sink even the largest ship?
        IT_JUST_MAY_BE_THAT_ISWEEN_WILL_BE                                            = 8725,  -- It just may be that Isween will be the tiny light that brings an end to this conflict.
        EVEN_THE_LARGEST_TREE_WAS_ONCE_A_SLENDER                                      = 8726,  -- Even the largest tree was once a slender sapling... I truly hope that he continues to grow in spirit.
        IT_WOULD_BE_WORTH_LOSING_MY_LIVELIHOOD_TO                                     = 8727,  -- It would be worth losing my livelihood to see an age without war.
        WHY_YOU_ASK                                                                   = 8728,  -- Why, you ask?
        EVERYONE_WANTS_TO_LIVE_THEIR_LIVES_WITHOUT_THE                                = 8729,  -- Everyone wants to live their lives without the threat of death hanging over them every second of the day...
        YOU_VE_HELPED_US_MORE_THAN_YOU_CAN                                            = 8730,  -- You've helped us more than you can know.
        OH_AND_TRY_TO_KEEP_MY_RELATIONS_WITH                                          = 8731,  -- Oh, and try to keep my relations with the Mamool Ja a secret, would you?
        HERE_S_A_LITTLE_SOMETHING_TO_GUARANTEE_YOUR                                   = 8732,  -- Here's a little something to guarantee your silence.
        THE_POTENTIAL_IS_READY_FOR_YOUR_INSPECTION                                    = 8733,  -- ... The potential is ready for your inspection.
        HIS_HER_COBALT_LEVELS_WERE_VERY_LOW_AND                                       = 8734,  -- His/Her] cobalt levels were very low, and I was afraid this would be another failure. But he/she] somehow clawed his/her] way back from the edge of death.
        HMPH_HIS_HER_ANSWERS_WERE_NOT_ENTIRELY_TRUTHFUL                               = 8735,  -- Hmph. His/Her] answers were not entirely truthful.
        YOU_WERE_THE_ONE_WHO_TRANSPLANTED_THIS                                        = 8736,  -- You were the one who transplanted this!
        THIS_LOATHSOME_AHRIMAN_LENS                                                   = 8737,  -- This... ...loathsome Ahriman lens!
        HOLD_YOUR_TONGUES_HE_SHE_AWAKENS                                              = 8738,  -- Hold your tongues. He/She] awakens...
        THE_LONG_GALLERY_REMAINS_DARK_IN_THE_GLOW                                     = 8739,  -- ... The long gallery remains dark in the glow of infinite lights. What meaning lies behind these words...?
        MY_APOLOGIES_I_BUT_PONDER_ALOUD_THE_MYSTERIES                                 = 8740,  -- My apologies. I but ponder aloud the mysteries of the universe. Pay me no heed.
        AH_A_VISITOR_FROM_FOREIGN_SHORES_GREETINGS_I                                  = 8741,  -- Ah, a visitor from foreign shores. Greetings. I am Waoud, a humble seer of Al Zahbi.
        I_DIVINE_FROM_YOUR_APPEARANCE_THAT_YOU_HAIL                                   = 8742,  -- I divine from your appearance that you hail from the western continent... A place we here know as the Middle Lands. An adventurer, yes?
        THE_EMPIRE_OF_AHT_URHGAN_RECRUITS_MERCENARIES_ON                              = 8743,  -- The Empire of Aht Urhgan recruits mercenaries on a grand scale, as she does all things. Our meager city has become a scurrying anthill of activity.
        BUT_YOU_DID_NOT_COME_TO_HEAR_SIMPLE                                           = 8744,  -- But you did not come to hear simple gossip. Destiny brought you to me, and it is of destiny I shall speak. I require less coin from adventurers for my divinations, considering their...uncertain employment.
        DO_YOU_WISH_TO_GAZE_ON_THE_TAPESTRY                                           = 8745,  -- Do you wish to gaze on the tapestry that fate has woven for you? I require less coin from adventurers for my divinations, considering their...uncertain employment.
        GAZE_ON_FATE_S_TAPESTRY_GAZE_AWAY_I                                           = 8746,  -- Gaze on fate's tapestry? Gaze away. I weave my own tapestry.
        A_PITY_PERHAPS_ANOTHER_TIME                                                   = 8747,  -- A pity. Perhaps another time.
        THE_MERCHANTS_OF_FOREIGN_LANDS_HAVE_A_SAYING                                  = 8748,  -- The merchants of foreign lands have a saying: Gil is the glue that brings us together.
        I_AM_AFRAID_YOUR_PURSE_IS_A_TRIFLE                                            = 8749,  -- I am afraid your purse is a trifle light today...
        MOST_EXCELLENT_I_SHALL_NOW_PROCEED_TO_ASK                                     = 8750,  -- Most excellent. I shall now proceed to ask you several questions.
        MY_DIVINATIONS_FOLLOW_A_SOMEWHAT_UNORTHODOX_PROCESS_ANSWER                    = 8751,  -- My divinations follow a somewhat unorthodox process. Answer truthfully and all shall be revealed.
        WHAT_IS_DESTINY                                                               = 8752,  -- What is destiny?
        DESTINY_IS_SOMETHING_THAT_IS_IMMUTABLE_ONE_FORGES                             = 8753,  -- Destiny is something that... Is immutable. One forges for oneself. Is unknowable.
        DOES_THE_ACCOMPLISHMENT_OF_A_GOAL_REQUIRE_SACRIFICE                           = 8754,  -- Does the accomplishment of a goal require sacrifice and hardship?
        DO_GOALS_REQUIRE_SACRIFICE_NOT_IF_YOU_THINK                                   = 8755,  -- Do goals require sacrifice? Not if you think hard enough. Occasionally. Absolutely.
        YOU_HOLD_IN_YOUR_HANDS_A_FORBIDDEN_SCROLL                                     = 8756,  -- You hold in your hands a forbidden scroll. Reading it will bring you untold wisdom, but cost all that you own.
        DO_YOU_READ_THE_SCROLL_THROW_THE_SCROLL                                       = 8757,  -- Do you... Read the scroll? Throw the scroll away? Burn the scroll?
        IF_THE_LOSS_OF_ONE_LIFE_WOULD_SAVE                                            = 8758,  -- If the loss of one life would save ten thousand, would you offer yourself without hesitation?
        OFFER_YOURSELF_OFFER_ANOTHER_I_HAVE_NO_SUCH                                   = 8759,  -- Offer yourself? Offer another... I have no such courage. Without hesitation.
        WOULD_YOU_CHOOSE_A_TUMULTUOUS_LIFE_WHERE_FAME                                 = 8760,  -- Would you choose a tumultuous life where fame or fortune were attainable, or a tranquil life where both were forever beyond your reach?
        WHICH_DO_YOU_CHOOSE_A_CHAOTIC_LIFE_A                                          = 8761,  -- Which do you choose? A chaotic life. A tranquil life. A mix of both.
        YOU_STAND_ON_THE_PRECIPICE_BETWEEN_LIFE_AND                                   = 8762,  -- You stand on the precipice between life and death. Would you choose to live life as a beast if it would save you from falling into the shadowy abyss of the underworld?
        WHAT_DO_YOU_DO_IF_IT_KEEPS_ME                                                 = 8763,  -- What do you do? If it keeps me from dying... Fall, and keep my humanity. Embrace life as a beast.
        A_COMPANION_IN_BATTLE_TURNS_AGAINST_YOU_RAISING                               = 8764,  -- A companion in battle turns against you, raising a weapon to attack.
        DO_YOU_BRACE_FOR_THE_BLOW_TRY_TO                                              = 8765,  -- Do you... Brace for the blow? Try to reason with him? Cut him down?
        A_LOVED_ONE_IS_AFFLICTED_WITH_A_TERRIBLE                                      = 8766,  -- A loved one is afflicted with a terrible illness and has little time left to live. You are asked to end that life by your own hand.
        DO_YOU_SEEK_A_CURE_LEAVE_THE_WORLD                                            = 8767,  -- Do you... Seek a cure? Leave the world together? Grant the request?
        YOU_ARE_IN_THE_MIDST_OF_A_FIERCE                                              = 8768,  -- You are in the midst of a fierce battle. The enemy lying at your feet was once a friend. His breath is ragged and weak.
        DO_YOU_TEND_TO_HIS_WOUNDS_END_HIS                                             = 8769,  -- Do you... Tend to his wounds? End his pain? Ignore your old friend?
        A_SUPERIOR_TO_WHOM_YOU_OWE_A_GREAT                                            = 8770,  -- A superior to whom you owe a great debt orders you to act in a way that violates your sense of justice.
        DO_YOU_TRY_TO_REMOVE_HIM_FROM_POWER                                           = 8771,  -- Do you... Try to remove him from power? Carry out the order? Follow your sense of justice?
        THANK_YOU_FOR_YOUR_PATIENCE_THE_ANSWERS_YOU                                   = 8772,  -- Thank you for your patience. The answers you have provided will be most helpful in my divination. Let us look upon what has been revealed...
        I_SEE_THE_SYMBOL_OF_THE_SKYSERPENT_IT                                         = 8773,  -- I see the symbol of the Skyserpent. It suggests spending some time away from battle.
        FOR_A_CHANGE_OF_PACE_WHY_NOT_TRY                                              = 8774,  -- For a change of pace, why not try your hand at harvesting in the Wajaom Woodlands or Bhaflau Thickets?
        YOU_MAY_MAKE_AN_UNEXPECTED_DISCOVERY                                          = 8775,  -- You may make an unexpected discovery.
        I_SEE_THE_SYMBOL_OF_THE_FLAMESERPENT_IT                                       = 8776,  -- I see the symbol of the Flameserpent. It suggests you take an aggressive stance and not shy away from a challenge.
        PERHAPS_YOU_MIGHT_TRY_VISITING_THE_COMMISSIONS_AGENCY                         = 8777,  -- Perhaps you might try visiting the Commissions Agency. A substantial reward could be yours for the taking.
        I_SEE_THE_SYMBOL_OF_THE_GALESERPENT_IT                                        = 8778,  -- I see the symbol of the Galeserpent. It suggests a loss in the near future...
        EVEN_I_CANNOT_PREDICT_WHAT_THIS_LOSS_MAY                                      = 8779,  -- Even I cannot predict what this loss may entail. You would do well to pay close attention to your possessions.
        I_SEE_THE_SYMBOL_OF_THE_STONESERPENT_IT                                       = 8780,  -- I see the symbol of the Stoneserpent. It suggests you will receive a boon from the earth.
        A_BOON_FROM_THE_EARTH_AH_YES_A                                                = 8781,  -- A boon from the earth...? Ah yes, a stint at mining may prove beneficial. All signs point towards Mount Zhayolm...
        I_SEE_THE_SYMBOL_OF_THE_SPRINGSERPENT_IT                                      = 8782,  -- I see the symbol of the Springserpent. It suggests a sojourn to the sea.
        YES_A_TRANQUIL_JOURNEY_ON_THE_WAVES_REPLACE                                   = 8783,  -- Yes, a tranquil journey on the waves. Replace your weapon with a fishing pole and fate will smile upon you.
        MY_DIVINATION_IS_OVER_I_TRUST_YOU_ARE                                         = 8784,  -- My divination is over. I trust you are satisfied?
        AS_DIVINING_IS_MY_STOCK_IN_TRADE_IT                                           = 8785,  -- As divining is my stock in trade, it may hardly surprise you to know that I believe destiny to be an ever flowing river of possibilities.
        YET_THERE_ARE_ALSO_THOSE_WHO_SEE_DESTINY                                      = 8786,  -- Yet there are also those who see destiny as immutable and inescapable. Which do you believe, I wonder...?
        BUT_I_DIGRESS_IF_YOU_DESIRE_TO_HEAR                                           = 8787,  -- ...But I digress. If you desire to hear my divinations again, return here after one full cycle of the sun.
        MAY_THE_TRUE_SERPENT_OF_WALAHRA_HOLD_YOU                                      = 8788,  -- May the True Serpent of Walahra hold you firmly in its coils...
        YOU_PAY_1000_GIL_FOR_THE_DIVINATION                                           = 8789,  -- You pay 1000 gil for the divination.
        SKY_FLAME_GALE_STONE_AND_SPRING_I_SEE                                         = 8790,  -- Sky, Flame, Gale, Stone, and Spring. I see all five serpent symbols... This sign heralds a turning point in your destiny.
        A_TIME_WILL_COME_WHEN_YOU_MUST_CHOOSE                                         = 8791,  -- A time will come when you must choose one of two paths. The road you walk will be entirely up to you...
        EVEN_I_CANNOT_ASCERTAIN_WHAT_AWAITS_YOU_AT                                    = 8792,  -- Even I cannot ascertain what awaits you at the end of each path. Yet one must be chosen nonetheless.
        THIS_CHOICE_CANNOT_BE_AVOIDED                                                 = 8793,  -- This choice cannot be avoided...
        MY_DIVINATION_IS_AT_AN_END_HAVE_I                                             = 8794,  -- ...My divination is at an end. Have I unsettled you?
        AHAHAHA_A_SEER_I_MAY_BE_BUT_I                                                 = 8795,  -- Ahahaha. A seer I may be, but I suggest you take these divinations with a light heart--no matter what the signs suggest.
        SHOULD_A_SIGN_PROVE_TO_BE_THE_GENTLE                                          = 8796,  -- Should a sign prove to be the gentle push that was needed, then consider it a blessing.
        NOW_COMES_THE_MATTER_OF_PAYMENT_I_AM                                          = 8797,  -- Now comes the matter of payment... I am told that an object of incredible rarity can be found in the Middle Lands.
        WOULD_YOU_CONSIDER_BRINGING_ME_THIS_PRIZE_IN                                  = 8798,  -- Would you consider bringing me this prize in place of common coin?
        TO_BE_TRUTHFUL_THE_ONE_WHO_WISHES_TO                                          = 8799,  -- To be truthful, the one who wishes to gaze upon this object is my own bedridden mother. A final wish from a curious old lady...
        DO_NOT_CONCERN_YOURSELF_WITH_HASTE_MY_DEAR                                    = 8800,  -- Do not concern yourself with haste. My dear mother clings to life with surprising ferocity.
        THE_OBJECT_OF_WHICH_I_SPEAK_IS_PRECIOUS                                       = 8801,  -- The object of which I speak is precious in the Near East, but worth precious little elsewhere...
        THE_TREASURE_I_WOULD_HAVE_YOU_SEEK_IS                                         = 8802,  -- The treasure I would have you seek is a jewel. It is said to glow with a bluish tint and be found near the bank of a certain river.
        THE_TREASURE_I_WOULD_HAVE_YOU_SEEK_IS_2                                       = 8803,  -- The treasure I would have you seek is a jewel. It is said to glow with a bluish tint and be found near the bank of a certain river.
        THE_TREASURE_I_WOULD_HAVE_YOU_SEEK_IS_3                                       = 8804,  -- The treasure I would have you seek is a pinch of golden sand. It is said to glow with the light of the sun and be found only on a certain beach.
        THE_TREASURE_I_WOULD_HAVE_YOU_SEEK_IS_4                                       = 8805,  -- The treasure I would have you seek is a pinch of golden sand. It is said to glow with the light of the sun and be found only on a certain beach.
        THE_TREASURE_I_WOULD_HAVE_YOU_SEEK_IS_5                                       = 8806,  -- The treasure I would have you seek is a precious stone. It is said to be as red as blood and found in a land of geysers.
        THE_TREASURE_I_WOULD_HAVE_YOU_SEEK_IS_6                                       = 8807,  -- The treasure I would have you seek is a precious stone. It is said to be as red as blood and found in a land of geysers.
        THE_DISCOVERY_OF_THIS_OBJECT_IS_APPARENTLY_MADE                               = 8808,  -- The discovery of this object is apparently made easier under very particular conditions, but I am not sufficiently familiar with the geography of your continent to even know where to start.
        I_CANNOT_PROVIDE_YOU_WITH_THE_NAME_OF                                         = 8809,  -- I cannot provide you with the name of this treasure, but perhaps with your knowledge...
        MY_APOLOGIES_YOU_DO_NOT_NEED_TO_HEAR                                          = 8810,  -- ...My apologies. You do not need to hear the woes of some street-corner fortuneteller.
        IN_FACT_I_SHALL_NOT_ASK_PAYMENT_OF                                            = 8811,  -- In fact, I shall not ask payment of you this day. And please forget my unreasonable request. May fortune smile upon you...
        AH_YOU_HAVE_RETURNED_I_HOPE_YOU_HAVE                                          = 8812,  -- Ah, you have returned. I hope you have forgotten our previous exchange. My words were hasty and ill-considered...
        YOUR_WORDS_HAVE_MOVED_ME_TO_ACTION_BEEN                                       = 8813,  -- Your words have... ...moved me to action. ...been forgotten.
        ARE_YOU_SURE_OF_THIS_A_THOUSAND_THOUSAND                                      = 8814,  -- Are you sure of this? A thousand thousand blessings on your house! I am speechless with gratitude...
        AGAIN_MY_APOLOGIES_I_KNOW_NOT_THE_NAME                                        = 8815,  -- Again, my apologies! I know not the name of the object, but I do remember some clues...
        ITS_DISCOVERY_IS_APPARENTLY_MADE_EASIER_UNDER_VERY                            = 8816,  -- Its discovery is apparently made easier under very particular conditions, but I cannot provide you with any details. My original source of information returned home to the Middle Lands before I could learn more.
        BUT_WITH_YOUR_KNOWLEDGE_OF_THAT_CONTINENT_YOU                                 = 8817,  -- But with your knowledge of that continent, you may have a chance...
        MAY_THE_WINDS_OF_FORTUNE_GUIDE_YOU                                            = 8818,  -- May the winds of fortune guide you!
        I_KNOW_NOT_THE_NAME_OF_THE_OBJECT                                             = 8819,  -- I know not the name of the object, but I do recall some clues...
        YES_THIS_IS_THE_WONDROUS_THE_TRAVELER_SPOKE                                   = 8820,  -- Yes! This is the wondrous % the traveler spoke of!
        AH_3                                                                          = 8821,  -- Ah...
        TO_BE_PERFECTLY_HONEST_IT_WAS_THE_MOTHER                                      = 8822,  -- To be perfectly honest, it was the mother of a colleague who wished to gaze upon this treasure...
        I_AM_AFRAID_I_HAVE_ANOTHER_FAVOR_TO                                           = 8823,  -- I am afraid I have another favor to ask you... Would you consent to deliver this to my colleague? I cannot leave the city, you see...
        A_THOUSAND_THOUSAND_APOLOGIES                                                 = 8824,  -- A thousand thousand apologies.
        MY_COLLEAGUE_IS_CURRENTLY_PART_OF_AN_IMPERIAL                                 = 8825,  -- My colleague is currently part of an Imperial patrol that apprehends desecrators of the ruins found in the Aydeewa Subterrane.
        THE_AYDEEWA_SUBTERRANE_RUNS_BENEATH_BHAFLAU_THICKETS_MAY                      = 8826,  -- The Aydeewa Subterrane runs beneath Bhaflau Thickets. May the winds of fortune guide you.
        DEBUG_YOUR_COBALT_VALUE_IS_PERCENT                                            = 8828,  -- DEBUG: Your cobalt value is # percent.
        DEBUG_YOUR_DIVINATION_RESULTS_ARE_NOW_BEYOND_THE                              = 8829,  -- DEBUG: Your divination results are now beyond the realm of mortal men. Lucky you.
        YOU_HAD_NO_REASON_TO_RETURN_HERE                                              = 8830,  -- You had no reason to return here...
        WHY_DO_YOU_STAND_BEFORE_ME                                                    = 8831,  -- Why do you stand before me...?
        YOU_HAVE_MADE_THE_SACRIFICE_AND_JOINED_THE                                    = 8832,  -- You have made the sacrifice and joined the ranks of the blue mages.
        WHAT_MORE_COULD_YOU_DESIRE_YOU_ARE_A                                          = 8833,  -- What more could you desire? You are a vessel, newly made...
        HOW_YOU_FILL_THAT_VESSEL_IS_ENTIRELY_UP                                       = 8834,  -- How you fill that vessel is entirely up to you.
        AS_YOU_PERFECT_THE_ARTS_OF_THE_BLUE                                           = 8835,  -- As you perfect the arts of the blue mage, you will feel blue magic taking root in your very bones.
        HOWEVER_ATTEMPTING_TO_HARNESS_A_POWER_THAT_OVERFLOWS                          = 8836,  -- However, attempting to harness a power that overflows your ability to hold it is a sure road to destruction...
        YOU_WOULD_DO_WELL_TO_REMEMBER_THAT                                            = 8837,  -- You would do well to remember that.
        SO_WHAT_ARE_YOU_TO_DO                                                         = 8838,  -- So what are you to do?
        HEHE_THE_ANSWER_IS_SIMPLE_GROW_IN_STRENGTH                                    = 8839,  -- Hehe... The answer is simple. Grow in strength until your body can withstand the power you desire. The vessel you have become can be tempered and expanded.
