        IN_ADDITION_YOU_WILL_ALSO_NEED_TO_BRING                                       = 9641,  -- In addition, you will also need to bring me a [white/black] mage scroll so I can program its data patterns into the head's control center.
        IF_POSSIBLE_LOCATE_HOWEVER_IF_THAT_PROVES_DIFFICULT                           = 9642,  -- If possible, locate %. However, if that proves difficult, % or % will suffice.
        WHEN_YOU_HAVE_READIED_ALL_THE_ITEMS_AND                                       = 9643,  -- When you have readied all the items and my fee, bring them here and I shall begin my work. However, please understand that programming artificial intelligence is not a simple thing. Many moons may pass before we are able to install your automaton's new head.
        THE_TURBAN_THE_SCROLL_AND_THE_COIN_YES                                        = 9644,  -- The turban, the scroll, and the coin. Yes, everything seems to be in order.
        I_SHALL_BEGIN_WORK_ON_YOUR_AUTOMATON_S                                        = 9645,  -- I shall begin work on your automaton's new head right away. As I mentioned before, programming artificial intelligence can prove remarkably time-consuming. I ask that you stop by every now and then to check on my progress...
        AND_MAYBE_BRING_A_CUP_OF_THE_EMPIRE                                           = 9646,  -- ...and maybe bring a cup of the Empire's finest roast when you do. Ahahaha!
        I_HAVE_JUST_BEGUN_WORKING_ON_YOUR_ORDER                                       = 9647,  -- I have just begun working on your order's artificial intelligence nodes. The road to completion is still long and winding.
        I_HAVE_MADE_MUCH_PROGRESS_IN_THE_AI                                           = 9648,  -- I have made much progress in the AI programming, but I still have much spell data to input.
        AH_GOOD_NEWS_THE_CRAFTSMAN_WHO_CARVES_ALL                                     = 9649,  -- Ah, good news, %! The craftsman who carves all my automaton heads dropped by yesterday morning with your order. Now I need only insert the control center and make a few minor adjustments. Our journey is almost over.
        YAWN_I_HAVE_HAD_SO_MUCH_WORK_THESE                                            = 9650,  -- <Yawn......> I have had so much work these past weeks... I can barely keep my eyes open, let alone my mind focused...
        AH_JUST_WHAT_THE_DOCTOR_ORDERED_YOUR_GENEROSITY                               = 9651,  -- Ah, just what the doctor ordered! Your generosity is much appreciated, %!
        AH_YOU_HAVE_COME_AT_A_GOOD_TIME                                               = 9652,  -- Ah, you have come at a good time, %. Your new head is complete!
        WITNESS_THE_SOULSOOTHER_C_1000_THE_PINNACLE_OF                                = 9653,  -- Witness the Soulsoother C-1000--the pinnacle of automaton technology--guaranteed to transform your companion into the perfect protector, the savvy savior, the ever-loyal leecher!
        WITNESS_THE_SPIRITREAVER_M_400_THE_PINNACLE_OF                                = 9654,  -- Witness the Spiritreaver M-400--the pinnacle of automaton technology--guaranteed to transform your companion into a deadly dealer of damage, a scheming spinner of spells, an unholy harbinger of hexes.
        THOUGH_WHETHER_YOUR_AUTOMATON_WILL_EVER_REALIZE_ITS                           = 9655,  -- Though, whether your automaton will ever realize its potential is completely up to you--its master. Forget this not, %.
        YOU_OBTAIN_THE_SOULSOOTHER_C_1000_HEAD                                        = 9656,  -- You obtain the Soulsoother C-1000 head!
        YOU_OBTAIN_THE_SPIRITREAVER_M_400_HEAD                                        = 9657,  -- You obtain the Spiritreaver M-400 head!
        AH_YOU_SEEM_MUCH_MORE_CONFIDENT_YOU_ARE                                       = 9658,  -- Ah...You seem much more confident. You are nearly one with %.
        EXCELLENT_IF_YOU_WISH_I_WILL_CONSTRUCT_YOU_2                                  = 9659,  -- Excellent, %. If you wish, I will construct you a new head for your automaton's Stormwaker Y-700 to optimize its efficiency in battle.
        AUTOMATONS_HAVE_IT_MADE_IT_WOULD_BE_NICE                                      = 9660,  -- Automatons have it made. It would be nice if we could also just equip an attachment and become a whole new person, wouldn't it?
        THEN_MAYBE_HE_WOULD_FINALLY_NOTICE_ME                                         = 9661,  -- Then maybe he would finally notice me...
        OH_I_M_SORRY_NO_YOU_DON_T                                                     = 9662,  -- Oh! I'm sorry. No, you don't need to know about that. I was just talking to myself...<blush>.
        WOW_YOU_VE_GOT_YOUR_VERY_OWN_AUTOMATON                                        = 9663,  -- Wow, you've got your very own automaton!
        BUT_YOU_NEED_TO_KNOW_THAT_THIS_BASIC                                          = 9664,  -- But you need to know that this basic model is like a newborn baby. It can't do anything until you help it grow.
        CUSTOMIZE_IT_WITH_ATTACHMENTS_AND_YOU_CAN_FINALLY                             = 9665,  -- Customize it with attachments, and you can finally bring out its true power!
        BUT_LET_ME_WARN_YOU                                                           = 9666,  -- But let me warn you...
        EVEN_IF_YOU_VE_ACQUIRED_AN_ATTACHMENT_FOR                                     = 9667,  -- Even if you've acquired an attachment for your automaton, it won't do you any good unless you know how to use it.
        IF_YOU_WOULD_LIKE_TO_CUSTOMIZE_YOU_MUST                                       = 9668,  -- If you would like to customize %, you must hand me the attachment you would like to equip.
        THEN_I_CAN_FIT_WITH_CONNECTORS_SO_THAT                                        = 9669,  -- Then I can fit % with connectors so that you can equip your new attachments.
        OKAY_NOW_THAT_I_VE_GOT_YOUR_LET                                               = 9670,  -- Okay, now that I've got your %, let me just plug in this connector here and...
        THAT_S_IT_NOW_YOU_SHOULD_BE_ABLE                                              = 9671,  -- That's it! Now you should be able to equip % with %.
        YOU_WILL_HAVE_TO_EQUIP_IT_AND_EXPERIMENT                                      = 9672,  -- You will have to equip it and experiment for yourself to see what features it adds to your automaton.
        YOU_CAN_NOW_EQUIP_YOUR_AUTOMATON_WITH                                         = 9673,  -- You can now equip your automaton with %.
        WHAT_S_THIS_IT_LOOKS_LIKE_I_VE                                                = 9674,  -- What's this? It looks like I've already fitted your automaton with the connector for that attachment.
        AH_HOW_KIND_OF_YOU_TO_VISIT_ME                                                = 9675,  -- Ah, %! How kind of you to visit me at my humble studio. Just applying the finishing touches to my latest work, here...
        ALL_I_NEED_IS_AHEM_THAT_ONE_PART                                              = 9676,  -- All I need is--<ahem>--that one part we spoke of, and this beauty will be complete. Yes, you should be able to find it around Mount Zhayolm, I'd wager.
        ANY_LUCK_HUNTING_DOWN_THAT_RARE_PART_FOR                                      = 9677,  -- Any luck hunting down that rare part for me? Hm? %, you say?
        THAT_S_A_TALL_ORDER_THERE_PERHAPS_YOU                                         = 9678,  -- That's a tall order, there. Perhaps you should seek out a veteran treasure hunter, or one acquainted with the environs.
        PHEW_ANOTHER_GRUELING_DAY_AT_THE_WORKSHOP_WHAT                                = 9679,  -- Phew! Another grueling day at the workshop. What's that? You've recovered the part for me?
        SPLENDID_I_M_JUST_ABOUT_TO_HEAD_OUT                                           = 9680,  -- Splendid! I'm just about to head out for the day, so if you could just deliver it to--<ahem>--the agreed-upon location, all should be in order.
        GREETINGS_I_HEARD_THAT_AH_A_CERTAIN_SOMEONE                                   = 9681,  -- Greetings, %. I heard that, ah, a certain someone's waiting for an opportunity to thank you in person. I was just--<ahem>--going to head over that way myself, so perhaps I'll see you there.
        GHATSAD_CAUTIOUSLY_SURVEYS_THE_ROOM                                           = 9682,  -- Ghatsad cautiously surveys the room.
        I_TELL_YOU_EVER_SINCE_LORD_RAZFAHD_RETURNED                                   = 9683,  -- (I tell you, %, ever since Lord Razfahd returned, her Majesty has been quite literally bounding about the palace in joy.)
        I_MUST_CONFESS_IT_BROUGHT_A_TEAR_TO                                           = 9684,  -- (I must confess, it brought a tear to this old Galka's eye as well.)
        I_DID_TUTOR_THE_BOY_AS_A_CHILD                                                = 9685,  -- (I did tutor the boy as a child, you know. Were it not beyond my station, why, I'd say I think of him almost as a son of my own.)
        IN_ANY_EVENT_WE_OWE_YOU_A_TRUE                                                = 9686,  -- (In any event, we owe you a true debt of gratitude. Thank you, %.)
        ORDERS_UPON_ORDERS_IT_S_ALL_WORK_AND                                          = 9687,  -- Orders upon orders! It's all work and no play for the busy puppetcrafter. My apologies, but could you return another time?
        OH_AND_THE_AHEM_BUSINESS_PARTNER_OF_WHOM                                      = 9688,  -- Oh, and %...the--<ahem>--business partner of whom we spoke said he's eagerly awaiting your arrival.
        A_DIVINE_RECEPTACLE_A_MARVEL_OF_SCIENCE_BORN                                  = 9689,  -- (A divine receptacle--a marvel of science, born of the centuries-long struggle of our forbears... Now we repair it, only to demolish it again like so much scrap metal.)
        HOW_FOOLISH_WE_WERE_TO_PRESUME_THAT_WE                                        = 9690,  -- (How foolish we were to presume that we--mere mortals--could wield the power of the divine. Still, there must be another way, and we will--no, we must--find it someday.)
        AH_BUT_FORGIVE_ME_I_M_SURE_YOU                                                = 9691,  -- (Ah, but forgive me, %. I'm sure you have more pressing matters to attend than one scientist's idle ramblings.)
        WE_SHALL_CALL_UPON_YOU_IF_WE_HAVE                                             = 9692,  -- (We shall call upon you if we have need of your services again. Until then, be well.)
