        IN_THE_PAST_WEEKS_THE_BARON_HAS_BEEN                                          = 12698,  -- In the past weeks, the baron has been focusing his research on the recently discovered Poroggo. He is currently planning a trip into Mamook to take a closer look at the new species.
        AND_THAT_IS_WHERE_THE_EMPIRE_REQUIRES_YOUR                                    = 12699,  -- And that is where the Empire requires your help. We need someone to act as a bodyguard for Professor Chanoix while he collects his data.
        YOU_NEED_WORRY_NOT_A_HEFTY_REWARD_WILL                                        = 12700,  -- You need worry not. A hefty reward will be provided for your services, in addition to the fame and glory you will receive by accepting such an important mission.
        WELL_WHAT_IS_YOUR_ANSWER_MERCENARY                                            = 12701,  -- Well, what is your answer, mercenary?
        ACCEPT_THE_JOB_YES_NOT_NOW                                                    = 12702,  -- Accept the job? Yes. Not now.
        UNDERSTOOD_HOWEVER_IF_YOU_HAVE_A_CHANGE_OF                                    = 12703,  -- Understood. However, if you have a change of heart, the position will remain open until we find another volunteer.
        WONDERFUL_I_WILL_CONTACT_THE_BARON_RIGHT_AWA                                  = 12704,  -- Wonderful. I will contact the baron right awa--
        AH_7                                                                          = 12705,  -- Ah!
        MAUDAAL_HAVE_YOU_NOT_YET_FOUND_ME_A                                           = 12706,  -- Maudaal. Have you not yet found me a bodyguard? I do grow weary of these gray walls and long to step back out into the wild woods of Wajaom.
        BARON_CHANOIX_YOUR_TIMING_IS_IMPECCABLE                                       = 12707,  -- Baron Chanoix! Your timing is impeccable!
        THIS_FINE_CITIZEN_HAS_JUST_VOLUNTEERED_FOR_THE                                = 12708,  -- This fine citizen has just volunteered for the position.
        EXCELLENT_NOW_I_CAN_FINALLY_CONTINUE_MY_RESEARCH                              = 12709,  -- Excellent! Now I can finally continue my research.
        FIRST_LET_ME_INFORM_YOU_OF_THE_FOCAL                                          = 12710,  -- First, let me inform you of the focal point of this expedition.
        ARE_YOU_FAMILIAR_WITH_THE_PECULIAR_BEASTMAN_KNOWN                             = 12711,  -- Are you familiar with the peculiar beastman known as the Poroggo?
        ARE_YOU_I_M_AN_EXPERT_PREGO                                                   = 12712,  -- Are you? I'm an expert! Prego?
        IS_THAT_SO_YOU_ADVENTURERS_NEVER_CEASE_TO                                     = 12713,  -- Is that so? You adventurers never cease to amaze me with your knowledge of the world.
        YOU_MEAN_TO_TELL_ME_THAT_YOU_HAVE                                             = 12714,  -- You mean to tell me that you have no prior knowledge of the Poroggo?
        AND_YOU_BELIEVE_THAT_THIS_UNEDUCATED_COMMONER_WILL                            = 12715,  -- And you believe that this uneducated commoner will be able to effectively assist me in my research?
        WELL_THAT_IS_OF_NO_MATTER_AT_LEAST                                            = 12716,  -- Well, that is of no matter. At least you were honest about your ignorance--unlike my friend Maudaal here...
        NOW_LISTEN_CAREFULLY_AS_I_SHALL_GIVE_YOU                                      = 12717,  -- Now listen carefully, as I shall give you a quick overview of the data I have collected thus far.
        YOU_HAD_BEST_WRITE_THIS_DOWN                                                  = 12718,  -- You had best write this down!
        YES_I_FIRST_CAME_ACROSS_THE_CREATURES_WHEN                                    = 12719,  -- Yes, I first came across the creatures when excavating a stratum of soil deep beneath Windurst Waters. In a layer we estimated to be nearly a hundred years old, my team discovered a large quantity of strangely shaped bones.
        AT_FIRST_GLANCE_THEY_RESEMBLED_THE_REMAINS_OF                                 = 12720,  -- At first glance, they resembled the remains of large toads. However...
        MEASUREMENTS_OF_THE_SKULLS_SHOWED_US_THAT_THE                                 = 12721,  -- Measurements of the skulls showed us that the creatures had exceptionally large brains.
        BUT_THAT_WAS_NOT_ALL_THE_FORELEGS_SEEMED                                      = 12722,  -- But that was not all--the forelegs seemed to be developed to the point that they might be used to grasp objects...
        WHEREAS_THE_HIND_LEGS_SEEMED_MORE_SUITED_FOR                                  = 12723,  -- Whereas the hind legs seemed more suited for walking than the traditional jumping one might expect from an amphibious land dweller.
        THAT_WAS_WHEN_I_REALIZED_THAT_WE_HAD                                          = 12724,  -- That was when I realized that we had not found the bones of a common toad, but a completely new and unique species!
        I_CAN_SENSE_WHAT_YOU_ARE_THINKING                                             = 12725,  -- I can sense what you are thinking...
        IT_WAS_AS_IF_WE_HAD_DISCOVERED_SOMETHING                                      = 12726,  -- It was as if we had discovered something directly from the pages of the well-known fairy tale, Poroggo and the Prince.
        AND_IT_IS_INDEED_FROM_THE_FAMOUS_FROG                                         = 12727,  -- And it is indeed from the famous frog princess, Poroggo, that we took the name for our new beastman.
        MY_THEORY_WAS_THAT_OVER_MILLIONS_OF_YEARS                                     = 12728,  -- My theory was that over millions of years, the toads of Sarutabaruta adapted to their surroundings and evolved into this higher life form.
        HOWEVER_2                                                                     = 12729,  -- However!
        I_IMMEDIATELY_TOOK_MY_FINDINGS_TO_THE_BOARD                                   = 12730,  -- I immediately took my findings to the Board of Akademia in Jeuno, but the fools simply laughed at me!
        YES_IT_IS_TRUE_I_HAD_NO_EXPLANATION                                           = 12731,  -- Yes, it is true, I had no explanation for the discovery of unevolved toad bones near those of the Poroggo...
        BUT_I_KNEW_THAT_THERE_HAD_TO_BE                                               = 12732,  -- But I knew that there had to be evidence that remained yet uncovered.
        THERE_HAD_TO_BE_A_MISSING_LINK_THAT                                           = 12733,  -- There had to be a missing link that would prove my theory!
        AND_THEN_ONE_DAY_WHILE_PORING_OVER_SOME                                       = 12734,  -- And then, one day while poring over some of the Optistery's more sensitive tomes, I came across a most intriguing passage.
        IT_SAID_THAT                                                                  = 12735,  -- It said that...
        THE_POROGGO_WE_FOUND_IN_WINDURST_WATERS                                       = 12736,  -- ...the Poroggo we found in Windurst Waters...
        THEY_WERE_ACTUALLY_TOADS_TRANSFORMED_INTO_HIDEOUS_CREATURES                   = 12737,  -- ...they were actually toads transformed into hideous creatures by the forbidden magicks of an eccentric mage named Samariri!
        IT_WAS_DIFFICULT_TO_ACCEPT_THAT_MY_ORIGINAL                                   = 12738,  -- It was difficult to accept that my original theory was incorrect.
        HOWEVER_AS_A_SCIENTIST_IT_WAS_THE_ONLY                                        = 12739,  -- However, as a scientist, it was the only choice with which I was left.
        AFTER_MY_FAILURE_IN_SARUTABARUTA_I_FELT_I                                     = 12740,  -- After my failure in Sarutabaruta, I felt I needed to put some distance between myself and the Middle Lands.
        AND_THAT_IS_WHEN_I_DECIDED_TO_PACK                                            = 12741,  -- And that is when I decided to pack up my equipment and ventured forth here, to Aradjiah, in search of new knowledge.
        AND_UNTIL_RECENTLY_I_HAVE_KEPT_MYSELF_QUIETLY                                 = 12742,  -- And until recently, I have kept myself quietly busy with studies of the colibri and the chigoe.
        THAT_IS_UNTIL_I_RECEIVED_WORD_OF_A                                            = 12743,  -- That is until I received word of a Poroggo sighting in the Mamool Ja Savagelands!
        ACCORDING_TO_THE_ANCIENT_TOME_I_FOUND_IN                                      = 12744,  -- According to the ancient tome I found in Windurst, all the Poroggo were exterminated by the Federation's mages immediately after their accidental creation. Though, ever since I discovered a peculiar footprint near the bungalow of my acquaintance, Pabool Ja, I have begun to believe otherwise.
        RECENTLY_THERE_HAVE_EVEN_BEEN_ADVENTURER_REPORTS_OF                           = 12745,  -- Recently, there have even been adventurer reports of toadlike creatures residing in the damper areas of the Mamool Ja stronghold.
        WHAT_I_WOULD_LIKE_TO_FIND_OUT_IS                                              = 12746,  -- What I would like to find out is where these beastmen came from.
        ARE_THEY_DESCENDANTS_OF_THE_POROGGO_SPAWNED_FROM                              = 12747,  -- Are they descendants of the Poroggo spawned from the spellweaving of some spoiled Tarutaru?
        OR_ARE_THEY_A_COMPLETELY_DIFFERENT_SPECIES_EVOLVED                            = 12748,  -- Or, are they a completely different species, evolved from mere toads as stated in my original theory?
        AND_HOW_ARE_THEY_ABLE_TO_TRANSFORM_THEIR                                      = 12749,  -- And! How are they able to transform their unexpecting victims into frogs?
        THE_ONLY_WAY_TO_COME_TO_SATISFACTORY_SCIENTIFIC                               = 12750,  -- The only way to come to satisfactory scientific conclusions is through research!
        AND_RESEARCH_REQUIRES_TIME                                                    = 12751,  -- And research requires time!!
        AND_SO_I_PLANNED_AN_EXPEDITION_INTO_THE                                       = 12752,  -- And so I planned an expedition into the savagelands to search out the elusive Poroggos and witness firsthand the instant a victim falls prey to their unique frog song.
        BUT_BEFORE_I_COULD_SET_OUT_ON_THIS                                            = 12753,  -- But before I could set out on this trip, I required a volunteer...
        TO_BE_THAT_VICTIM                                                             = 12754,  -- ...to be that victim!
        AH_I_M_SORRY_IF_I_ALARMED_YOU                                                 = 12755,  -- Ah, I'm sorry if I alarmed you. Your services will only be required to fend off...unwanted guests.
        THE_NOBLE_SALWA_MOLWA_WILL_BE_OUR_GUINEA                                      = 12756,  -- The noble Salwa-Molwa will be our guinea...er...toad.
        SO_THIS_IS_OUR_MIGHTY_MERCENARY_LOOKS_A                                       = 12757,  -- So this is our mighty mercenary? Looks a bit scrawny, if you ask me.
